					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Gaṇapatidēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1175, Vaiśākha Saptami, Sunday <hi rend="italic">(divasakṛid-vāramu)</hi></hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1253 A.D. April 7, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Partly built in. Seems to record the installation of an image of Garuḍa by a certain Māraṇḍu of chaturtha-vaṁśa. It also mentions <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāni Sarvādhikāri</hi> Māyidēva-pregaḍa, an official under a chief (name lost) of Addaṅki, who was a subordinate of the Kākatīya Gaṇapati.</p>						

						</summary>
